<pre><code>class A1 {     int a = 87;      String doA() {         return "a1";     } }  public class B2 extends A1 {     int a = 99;      String doA() {         return "b1";     }      public static void main(String[] args) {         A1 ab = new B2();         System.out.println(ab.getClass());         System.out.println(ab.a);         System.out.println(ab.doA());      } } </code></pre>  <p>output:</p>  <pre><code>class com.pack.B2 87 b1 </code></pre>  <p>In the above program i am using the method overriding which resolves at runtime. That is confirmed by printing the getClass of the object. How come it prints the value of varible in class A1 instead the B2 class's variable? </p>